Here is the AI Import Assessment. The platform reads the cycle in context, then produces a written summary in plain language — what happened, what it means, and what the Risk Manager should do next. This is generated automatically every cycle.
Behind this is an AI Builder prompt running on Microsoft's Azure OpenAI service. The platform passes the cycle's data and a structured prompt — the prompt tells the AI to act as a Risk Manager, explain warnings, and recommend next steps. The AI's output is written back into this field.
